World Bank Loans $172 Million for Bangladesh Solar Homes Project

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-10-05T09:31:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/world-bank-loans-172-million-for-bangladesh-solar-homes-project.html
The  World Bank  approved $172 million
of credit to install solar power systems in 630,000 homes in
rural  Bangladesh  that lack connections to the electricity grid.  State-run Infrastructure Development Co. will install the
systems in 2012, the bank said in a  statement  on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  